","user":{"login":"astralbat","id":5352772,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzNTI3NzI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5352772?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat","html_url":"https://github.com/astralbat","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-01-30T09:35:24Z","updated_at":"2025-01-30T09:37:06Z","body":"I'm also getting files constantly resynced between two machines: one Linux/ZFS, the other an iMac with modifications being claimed on both sides. I can cause all these files in a small folder to be 'modified' on-demand by simply pressing \"Rescan\".\n\nI can get this to stop if I stop syncing ownership. I.e. hitting \"Rescan\" doesn't sync anything. Unlike the author, I haven't tried changing my uids/gids to match.\n\nI followed the Syncthing documentation regarding owner sync. I have setup for each file in this small folder:\n* iMac: Uid=501/mark, Gid=20/staff\n* Linux: Uid=3000/mark, Gid=50/staff\n\nSyncthing is doing the right thing for me in finding an alternative Uid/Gid to match on the Linux side as I sync primarily from iMac -> Linux.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/2623974230/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rock