ers/astralbat/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astralbat/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-02-03T09:24:50Z","updated_at":"2025-02-03T09:24:50Z","body":"I wonder now whether change times might not be the issue here. They don't appear to be stored in the database, thus the global version seems to have a change time of 0 and won't trigger a rescan. This would make sense with my testing showing that the syncing of extended attributes not being a problem.\n\nFurther down however:\nhttps://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/blob/b300c297c666e79a5aec502f80f9335330e54d34/lib/protocol/bep_fileinfo.go#L441-L448\n\nAnd:\nhttps://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/blob/b300c297c666e79a5aec502f80f9335330e54d34/lib/protocol/bep_fileinfo.go#L845-L855\n\nWhich I think is what the poster is referring to. For me also, I am syncing between Linux and Darwin platforms, so the platforms are different.\n\nSyncthing has a very good feature where it will look up the uid/gid on the destination side, but that intellegence is lost here. I am not going to submit a pull request, but it seems that syncthing should be storing the uids and gids on both sides to make a better comparison. Right now this seems like a lost feature and the workaround is to make sure they are the same, at least when the unix platforms are different.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/2630395706/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"astralbat","id":5352772,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzNTI3NzI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5352772?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/use