5zZTE0"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":true,"topics":["go","p2p","peer-to-peer","synchronization"],"visibility":"public","forks":4825,"open_issues":361,"watchers":77447,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/pulls/10176","html_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/10176","diff_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/10176.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/10176.patch","merged_at":"2025-06-16T15:12:34Z"},"body":"Only Require either matching UID & GID OR matching Names.\r\n\r\nIf the 2 devices have a different Name => UID mapping, they can never be totaly equal. Therefore when syncing we try matching the Name and fall back to the UID. However when scanning for changes we currently require both the Name & UID to match. This leads to forever having out of sync files back and forth, or local additions when receive only.\r\n\r\nThis patch does not change the sending behavoir. It only change what we decide is equal for exisiting files with mismapped Name => UID,\r\n\r\nThe added testcases show the change: Test 1,5,6 are the same as current. Test 2,3 Are what change with this patch (from false to true). Test 4 is a subset of test 2 they is currently special cased as true, which does not chnage.\r\n\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/10176/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/10176/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":18172815940,"node_id":"CE_lADOAOCAEs6j42UyzwAAAAQ7LypE","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/events/18172815940","actor":{"login":"calmh","id":125426,"node_id